Class TailArrayQueue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractQueue<E>
        • java.util.concurrent.ArrayBlockingQueue<E>
          • org.minijson.common.TailArrayQueue<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, BlockingQueue<E>, Queue<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JsonNodeBuffer, JsonTokenBuffer

    public class TailArrayQueue<E>
extends ArrayBlockingQueue<E>
    A "tail buffer". It keeps the finite number of objects that have been added last. Implemented by a ring buffer. TailArrayQueue can be used to keep the "last X objects that have been read" while reading an object stream. (Note: the implementation is not thread-safe.)
